The paper discusses representation learning, which is a central focus in artificial intelligence, and specifically focuses on factorial representations. The paper also discusses various constraints that encourage a learning algorithm to discover factorial representations, which suggests a focus on machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
